title: ARLC Chairman hits back at Premier over stadium remarks
description: ARLC Chairman Peter V'landys hits back at Premier Dominic Perrottet's stadium remarks.

title: ‘Have you seen this vampire?’: Beloved cardboard cut-out stolen from Melbourne cinema
description: It’s a case of Twilight robbery as a four-person team pull off a daring heist to steal a vintage Edward Cullen cardboard cut-out.

title: ‘Complete spin’: V’landys reveals grand final deadline in scathing attack on Perrottet
description: The Australian Rugby League Commission boss hinted the NRL might even keep the grand final in Sydney to hold up their end of the bargain in his latest attack on the NSW government.

author: Josh Butler
title: Labor’s housing minister vows to do more to fix homelessness as ‘serious’ crisis spreads
description: Julie Collins says ‘we need to be ambitious’ on housing as she commits to greater national leadership and cooperation with statesGet our free news app, morning email briefing or daily news podcastThe federal housing minister, Julie Collins, has promised a greater leadership role from the commonwealth to address homelessness, as social advocates warn skyrocketing rental prices are forcing families to live in tents.The minister admitted Australia has “a really serious housing affordability challenge”, with key Labor policies for homebuyers and public housing not likely to open until early...

title: Piastri rejects Alpine F1 drive
description: Oscar Piastri has turned down a Formula 1 race drive with Alpine for 2023, in a move that has shocked the sport.

author: Cameron Atfield
title: Twice in a lifetime? Queensland ready to pounce for NRL grand final
description: As the NRL goes to war with the NSW government over stadium funding, Queensland is poised to poach the grand final from its traditional home for a second straight year.

author: Tony Harper
title: Rugby News: ‘Bugger’ – Dave Rennie update after Samu Kerevi disaster, Boks legend says Cane ‘not in best 15’
description: Wallabies coach Dave Rennie said Samu Kerevi remains in World Cup calculations despite the season-ending ACL injury suffered at the Commonwealth Games. title: Win for Territories on equal rights
description: A Bill to allow the ACT and NT to make their own laws such as legalising voluntary assisted dying has passed the House of Representatives, and Territory politicians have urged their Senate colleagues to vote in favour of it too.

author: Graham Readfearn
title: John Howard’s climate doubts reveal more about conservative identity politics than anything else | Temperature Check
description: The latest comments from the former PM, who once said he was ‘agnostic’ on climate change, remind us some remain unmoved by scienceThe former prime minister John Howard remains an elder statesman among conservatives so when he’s asked on primetime television if he doubts that climate change is happening, his response is revealing.That moment happened on the ABC on Tuesday evening during an interview with actor David Wenham, who asked: “You’re not refuting the fact that there’s climate change?” Continue reading...

author: Iain Payten
title: Pollard called up to Wallabies after Porecki ruled out with concussion
description: Twenty-year-old Brumbies hooker Billy Pollard is on his way to Argentina after starting Wallabies hooker Dave Porecki suffered a head knock at training.
